---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const meta = {
  title: 'Durable vs WordPress: AI Builder vs Classic CMS',
  description: 'Durable generates complete websites in 30 seconds with AI-written content. WordPress is powerful but complex. Durable $15+/mo, WordPress varies by hosting. Side-by-side comparison.',
  image: '/og-image.svg',
  keywords: ['Durable vs WordPress', 'AI website builder vs WordPress', 'Durable review', 'WordPress alternative', 'AI website builder'],
};
---

<Layout {...meta}>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-[#0099FF]/5 to-[#9333EA]/5 py-12 sm:py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
      <p class="text-[10px] sm:text-xs font-black text-[#0099FF] mb-4 tracking-[0.3em] uppercase">
        AI Tool Comparison · 2025 Updated
      </p>

      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-black mb-6 leading-tight">
        Durable vs WordPress
      </h1>

      <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-700 mb-8">
        Durable and WordPress couldn't be more different. Durable is an AI-powered website builder that generates complete sites in 30 seconds. WordPress is a powerful CMS that runs 43% of the web but requires technical skills. Durable is fast and easy. WordPress is flexible but complex. They serve completely different users.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-white bg-opacity-50 border-2 border-gray-300 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
          Quick answer: Choose Durable if you want a complete website fast without touching code. Choose WordPress if you need full control, unlimited customization, and you're willing to learn or hire developers. Durable is $15+/month. WordPress is free but hosting costs $3-50+/month. Durable takes 30 seconds. WordPress takes days or weeks.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- At a Glance -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Durable vs WordPress At a Glance
    </h2>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="bg-gray-100">
            <th class="text-left p-4 font-bold"></th>
            <th class="text-left p-4 font-bold">Durable</th>
            <th class="text-left p-4 font-bold">WordPress</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Best for</td>
            <td class="p-4">Service businesses, beginners</td>
            <td class="p-4">Everyone (with technical skills or budget)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Setup time</td>
            <td class="p-4">30 seconds</td>
            <td class="p-4">Hours to weeks</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Technical skills</td>
            <td class="p-4">None required</td>
            <td class="p-4">Medium to high</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Customization</td>
            <td class="p-4">Limited (AI-generated)</td>
            <td class="p-4">Unlimited (code-level access)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Cost</td>
            <td class="p-4">$15/month</td>
            <td class="p-4">Free + hosting ($3-50/mo)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Scalability</td>
            <td class="p-4">Limited</td>
            <td class="p-4">Excellent</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Plugins</td>
            <td class="p-4">No (built-in features only)</td>
            <td class="p-4">60,000+ plugins</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">You own the site</td>
            <td class="p-4">No (hosted on Durable)</td>
            <td class="p-4">Yes (self-hosted)</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Durable Overview -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      What Durable Does Best
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">1. Instant Website Generation</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Durable generates complete websites:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>30 seconds:</strong> Tell AI your business, get full website</li>
          <li>• <strong>Multiple pages:</strong> Home, services, about, contact</li>
          <li>• <strong>AI-written content:</strong> Professional copy for your industry</li>
          <li>• <strong>Service-specific:</strong> Knows what plumbers/consultants need</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Best for:</strong> Service businesses who need a site fast and don't want to touch code.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">2. Zero Technical Skills Required</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Anyone can use Durable:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>No hosting setup:</strong> Durable handles everything</li>
          <li>• <strong>No domain configuration:</strong> Buy through Durable or connect yours</li>
            <li>• <strong>No plugins to manage:</strong> Features built-in</li>
          <li>• <strong>No updates to run:</strong> Durable handles security</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Best for:</strong> Non-technical users who want to avoid complexity.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">3. Built-in Business Tools</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Durable includes more than websites:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>CRM:</strong> Manage customers and leads</li>
          <li>• <strong>Invoicing:</strong> Create and send invoices</li>
          <li>• <strong>AI assistant:</strong> Help with business tasks</li>
          <li>• <strong>Analytics:</strong> See who visits your site</li>
          <li>• <strong>Booking:</strong> Customers can schedule appointments</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Best for:</strong> Small businesses who want all-in-one solution.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">4. AI-First Approach</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Everything uses AI:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Conversational:</strong> Tell AI what you need</li>
          <li>• <strong>Iterative:</strong> Ask AI to refine, add, change content</li>
          <li>• <strong>Smart suggestions:</strong> AI recommends improvements</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Best for:</strong> People who want AI to do the heavy lifting.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WordPress Overview -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      What WordPress Does Best
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">1. Unlimited Flexibility</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">WordPress can do anything:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Any feature:</strong> 60,000+ plugins extend functionality</li>
          <li>• <strong>Any design:</strong> Thousands of themes, full code access</li>
          <li>• <strong>Any scale:</strong> From small blogs to enterprise sites</li>
          <li>• <strong>Ecommerce:</strong> WooCommerce powers millions of stores</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Best for:</strong> Projects that need custom features or unique designs.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">2. You Own Everything</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">WordPress is self-hosted:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Your data:</strong> Complete control over content</li>
          <li>• <strong>Your code:</strong> Customize anything</li>
          <li>• <strong>Your hosting:</strong> Choose any provider</li>
          <li>• <strong>Portable:</strong> Move your site anywhere</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Best for:</strong> People who want full control and ownership.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">3. Massive Ecosystem</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">WordPress has everything:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Plugins:</strong> Add any feature imaginable</li>
          <li>• <strong>Themes:</strong> Any design style you want</li>
          <li>• <strong>Developers:</strong> Easy to find WordPress experts</li>
          <li>• <strong>Resources:</strong> Tutorials, forums, help everywhere</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Best for:</strong> Long-term projects that might need custom development.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">4. SEO Powerhouse</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">WordPress is built for SEO:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Yoast/RankMath:</strong> Powerful SEO plugins</li>
          <li>• <strong>Clean code:</strong> Search engines love WordPress</li>
          <li>• <strong>Fast loading:</strong> With proper optimization</li>
          <li>• <strong>Blogging native:</strong> Built for content marketing</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Best for:</strong> Content-heavy sites and SEO-focused businesses.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Use Cases -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      When to Choose Each
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Choose Durable if:</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• You're service business (plumber, consultant, agency)</li>
          <li>• You need a website today (not next week)</li>
          <li>• You don't want to learn technical skills</li>
          <li>• You want AI to generate content for you</li>
          <li>• You need CRM/invoicing built-in</li>
          <li>• You have simple needs and want to move on</li>
          <li>• You don't care about unlimited customization</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Choose WordPress if:</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• You need custom features WordPress can do anything</li>
          <li>• You want full control over design and functionality</li>
          <li>• You're building something complex (ecommerce, membership, etc.)</li>
          <li>• You plan to scale significantly</li>
          <li>• You have developer skills or budget to hire</li>
          <li>• You care about SEO and content marketing</li>
          <li>• You want to own your site completely</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Feature Comparison -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Feature Comparison
    </h2>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="bg-gray-100">
            <th class="text-left p-4 font-bold">Feature</th>
            <th class="text-left p-4 font-bold">Durable</th>
            <th class="text-left p-4 font-bold">WordPress</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Setup time</td>
            <td class="p-4">30 seconds</td>
            <td class="p-4">Hours to weeks</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Technical skills</td>
            <td class="p-4">None</td>
            <td class="p-4">Medium to high</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Customization</td>
            <td class="p-4">Limited</td>
            <td class="p-4">Unlimited</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">AI generation</td>
            <td class="p-4">Full (site + content)</td>
            <td class="p-4">Via plugins (limited)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Plugins/Extensions</td>
            <td class="p-4">No</td>
            <td class="p-4">60,000+</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Themes</td>
            <td class="p-4">Few</td>
            <td class="p-4">Thousands</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Ecommerce</td>
            <td class="p-4">No (booking only)</td>
            <td class="p-4">Yes (WooCommerce)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Blogging</td>
            <td class="p-4">No</td>
            <td class="p-4">Yes (native)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">SEO tools</td>
            <td class="p-4">Basic</td>
            <td class="p-4">Advanced (plugins)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">CRM</td>
            <td class="p-4">Yes (built-in)</td>
            <td class="p-4">No (needs plugin)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">You own site</td>
            <td class="p-4">No</td>
            <td class="p-4">Yes</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Hosting included</td>
            <td class="p-4">Yes</td>
            <td class="p-4">No (separate)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Updates/Security</td>
            <td class="p-4">Durable handles</td>
            <td class="p-4">You manage</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Starting price</td>
            <td class="p-14">$15/month</td>
            <td class="p-14">Free + hosting ($3-50/mo)</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Cost Comparison -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Cost Breakdown
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Durable Pricing</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Starter:</strong> $15/month - Basic website</li>
          <li>• <strong>Business:</strong> $25/month - More features</li>
          <li>• <strong>Mogul:</strong> $80/month - Multiple sites</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Includes:</strong> Hosting, domain (extra), SSL, AI generation, CRM, invoicing.</p>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Total cost:</strong> $15-80/month. All-inclusive.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">WordPress Pricing</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Software:</strong> Free</li>
          <li>• <strong>Hosting:</strong> $3-50/month depending on needs</li>
          <li>• <strong>Domain:</strong> $10-15/year</li>
          <li>• <strong>Premium theme:</strong> $0-100 (one-time)</li>
          <li>• <strong>Plugins:</strong> Many free, premium plugins cost extra</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Total cost:</strong> $5-100+/month depending on plugins and hosting.</p>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Note:</strong> WordPress gets expensive if you need premium plugins or managed hosting.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Bottom Line -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <div class="bg-white bg-opacity-50 border-2 border-gray-300 rounded-xl p-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-black mb-6">Bottom Line</h2>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">Durable and WordPress are completely different tools for completely different needs.</p>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6"><strong>Choose Durable if you want:</strong></p>
      <ul class="space-y-3 mb-6">
        <li>• A complete website in 30 seconds</li>
        <li>• Zero technical headaches</li>
        <li>• AI to generate content and design</li>
        <li>• Built-in business tools (CRM, invoicing)</li>
        <li>• Simple, predictable pricing</li>
        <li>• To move on to running your business</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6"><strong>Choose WordPress if you want:</strong></p>
      <ul class="space-y-3 mb-6">
        <li>• Unlimited customization possibilities</li>
        <li>• Full control and ownership</li>
        <li>• To build something unique or complex</li>
        <li>• Access to 60,000+ plugins</li>
        <li>• Best-in-class SEO and blogging</li>
        <li>• To scale without platform limitations</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700"><strong>Can't go wrong either way:</strong> Both have free trials or demos. Try Durable for instant results. Try WordPress (via WordPress.com or local install) to see if you're comfortable with the complexity. The right choice depends on your technical comfort, timeline, and long-term goals.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Related -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black mb-6 text-gray-900">
      Related Comparisons
    </h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <a href="/webflow-vs-wordpress" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Webflow vs WordPress</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">No-code vs classic CMS</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/framer-vs-durable" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Framer vs Durable</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Design-focused vs AI-first</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
